headline: Amazon signs up FedEx for residential deliveries
summary: The Memphis-based delivery company said the multi-year agreement covers residential delivery of select large packages for Amazon.  The deal with FedEx, signed in February, gives Amazon "cost favorability" compared with delivery rival UPS, Business Insider had reported, citing an internal document.
